The paper deals with the computational complexity of deciding whether a given chemical reaction network satisfies different definitions of atomicity. This involves analyzing the structure of the network and its properties, which is a typical topic in computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The study of chemical reaction networks can be seen as a control problem, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of decision problems, which is relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
